e a dynamic access report for the `ServletWrappingController` and its test class. Making an existing placeholder public is on my mind, but I’m not so sure. I might have to consider the native image—reflection could get tricky without a user filter, but maybe I could use an anonymous subclass of `ServletWrappingController`. It seems like `RecordingServlet` could serve as a top-level test class, but I have to follow the rules about public classes and file naming conventions. There's something about metadata generation from reflection that might get complicated too, especially with certain filters in place.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining test source roots and metadata**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the \\\"resolved target test source root,\\\" which could possibly be `tests/src/.../src/test/java`. The phrasing suggests focusing only on tests, so I'm cautious about editing non-test files. The test does reflect on the application class, but the goal is to gather library metadata rather than application metadata. I’m realizing that if users want to configure their own servlet for the `ServletWrappingController`, it means including application-specific metadata is essential. Then, while aiming for a native image, the TCK could include test metadata via the agent, but I must be careful not to pollute the generated metadata with unnecessary app classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering reflection metadata**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how using the test class would generate reflection metadata for the target, but that wouldn't be considered library metadata. Perhaps the TCK conditional metadata could be accepted, but the generated metadata is meant to update the library metadata externally. My focus is on ensuring that the library doesn’t miss crucial metadata. I wonder if I should use a servlet class from a non-test dependency instead, like `org.springframework.web.servlet.DispatcherServlet`, so that the metadata remains relevant to the library and its context.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_EqZ4AzE9FjajT3KvBvCNNi3q|fc_0557a2e3a0d0d8ab016a264a8b6e4c819494eaaa3b197d8b3a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"class AbstractController|class WebContentGenerator|setServletContext|extends WebApplicationObjectSupport\" ../../source_context/org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18/main/extracted/org/springframework/web/servlet -n | head -80"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 715, "output": 674, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35181, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780894332124, "responseId": "resp_0557a2e3a0d0d8ab016a264a7c9c608194a669e1fd80787ea3"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_EqZ4AzE9FjajT3KvBvCNNi3q|fc_0557a2e3a0d0d8ab016a264a8b6e4c819494eaaa3b197d8b3a", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "../../source_context/org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18/main/extracted/org/springframework/web/servlet/FrameworkServlet.java:687:\t\twac.setServletContext(getServletContext());\n../../source_context/org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18/main/extracted/org/springframework/web/servlet/support/WebContentGenerator.java:67:public abstract class WebContentGenerator extends WebApplicationObjectSupport {\n../../source_context/org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18/main/extracted/org/springframework/web/servlet/handler/SimpleServletPostProcessor.java:93:\tpublic void setServletContext(ServletContext servletContext) {\n../../source_context/org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18/main/extracted/org/springframework/web/servlet/view/BeanNameViewResolver.java:45:public class BeanNameViewResolver extends WebApplicationObjectSupport implements ViewResolver, Ordered {\n../../source_context/org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18/main/extracted/org/springframework/web/servlet/resource/Defa